logy and political economy with workplace studies and uses examples of legal and illegal activity to demonstrate the multiple harms within the service economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh1 aPantazis, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPemberton, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTombs, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311119666440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529204025423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529204025/original  a978-3-11-119666-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles